<HEADLINE>
FT  02 JUL 93 / London Stock Exchange: Hillsdown ahead
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By STEVE THOMPSON, JOEL KIBAZO and CHRISTOPHER PRICE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
In a perky food manufacturing sector, Hillsdown Holdings led the way forward
as the group said trading was in line with market expectations and that
interim operating profits to June would be at least Pounds 80m against
Pounds 81.8m last year. Dealers said there was a considerable relief factor
that Hillsdown had made a good recovery from its problems. Last year's
profits were dented by oversupply in the chicken market. Hillsdown shares
added 7 to 144p on hefty turnover of 13m.
A rumoured review of the food manufacturing stocks, said to be by UBS, added
spice to the sector which has languished in the doldrums in recent sessions.
Associated British Food gained 5 to 489p, Booker 6 to 393p, and
Cadbury-Schweppes 3 to 467p. Devro International's second day in the market
brought further rewards, the shares adding 6 to 199p. They came to the
market at 170p on Wednesday.
