<HEADLINE>
FT  02 JUL 93 / International Company News: US agribusiness groups agree
joint venture terms
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LAURIE MORSE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   CHICAGO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
ILLINOIS-BASED IMC Fertilizer Group and Freeport-McMoRan Resources Partners
have finalised the combination of their phosphate fertiliser businesses.
The joint venture, to be called IMC-Agrico company, becomes one of the
largest phosphate fertiliser operations in the world, and represents about
30 per cent of US market share.
The venture, first announced in January, is expected to achieve about
Dollars 95m in cost savings for the two companies. Estimated sales for the
company are Dollars 1bn, and combined phosphate rock capacity will be about
30m tons a year.
The consolidation was driven by a long-term slump in world fertiliser
prices. World prices are at 20-year lows, in part because the former states
of the Soviet Union have been aggressively marketing their phosphate
resources internationally.
India and China have also reduced their central purchases of the commodity,
and demand has been curtailed in eastern and western Europe because of
economic slumps and agricultural reforms.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
<CO>IMC Fertilizer Group.
    Freeport-McMoRan Resources Partners.
    IMC-Agrico.
</CO>
<XX>
Countries:-
