<HEADLINE>
FT  02 JUL 93 / UK Company News: Warburg top in survey
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD GOURLAY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
SG WARBURG Securities took the title of top stockbroking research company
for the third year running in Extel's 1993 Survey of Financial Analysts.
James Capel, which dominated the awards for the entire 1980s, reclaimed the
number two slot from NatWest Securities which slipped to third.
Extel had replies to its survey from 122 fund managers who collectively
manage Pounds 725bn of funds.
UBS slipped furthest, from 4th to 6th position and was voted as having shown
the most deterioration in quality of research. Credit Lyonnais Laing (10th)
and Smith New Court (7th) showed the greatest quality improvement and were
only a few votes short of UBS.
Kleinwort Benson's water team won Extel's 'all stars' team award for the
highest number of votes in any sector.
