FT  02 JUL 93 / Parliament and Politics: Brown calls for interest rate cut
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BRITAIN SHOULD cut its interest rates in line with the reduction in the cost
of borrowing in Germany, Mr Gordon Brown, Labour's Treasury spokesman, said
last night.
Speaking after the Treasury and Bank of England refused to follow the
Bundesbank's decision to cut Germany's discount rate, Mr Brown signalled a
fresh attempt by Labour to set the pace at Westminster in debate on the
economy.
