<HEADLINE>
FT  02 JUL 93 / Taurus vs Crest: How they compare
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
 ----------------------------------------------------------------------
TAURUS
 ----------------------------------------------------------------------
All shareholders required to use system
No option to retain certificates
Settlement and free 'custody' service available for private investors,
with less flexibility
Complex stock holding and transfer mechanisms
Very high security and large compensation scheme, on account of
comprehensiveness of system
Operator as conduit for most information and benefits Structure
Periodic register updates; ownership rights in the interim, largely
dependent on system records
Legal environment complex, increased by new entitlement concept
System sought to automate complex and often manual procedures
Overnight batch settlement
Assured payments addressed late in development process
 ----------------------------------------------------------------------
CREST
 ----------------------------------------------------------------------
Membership optional
Certificates may be retained by shareholders
Investor choice: uncertificated holding and transfer with option to
hold certificates
Relatively straightforward structure for ownership and transfer of
securities
Less overbearing requirements in an environment of choice
System will provide fewer 'custodial' functions Structure
Daily register updates promptly after settlement; legal ownership
rights evidenced by the entry on the company register
Should require far less new law, and in more familiar areas
Seeks to address key causes of market complexity and thus reduce it
Continuous settlement with same-day functionality
Possible 'cash on delivery' mechanism
 ----------------------------------------------------------------------
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ   United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
</XX>
