<HEADLINE>
FT  02 JUL 93 / Recovery in west Midlands 'slows'
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL CHEESERIGHT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE PACE of recovery among west Midlands manufacturers and service companies
has slowed over the past three months, the latest survey of 580 companies by
the regional group of Chambers of Commerce shows, Paul Cheeseright writes.
The growth in orders reported by companies in the first quarter of the year
petered out between March and June, emphasising that the movement out of
recession remains tentative.
The survey, published today, shows that in June 32 per cent of manufacturing
companies had more domestic and export orders than three months before. Yet
this is scarcely changed from March when companies were reporting a marked
upturn in orders compared with last December.
The same trend is apparent with service companies, among which the
proportion working at full capacity dropped between March and June from 22
per cent to 17 per cent. Among manufacturers, 86 per cent of companies are
working at less than 80 per cent of capacity.
</TEXT>
