range from Dollars 10bn to Dollars 20bn since mid-1987 when Taipei began to
lift restrictions on contacts with the mainland.
Data from the Central Bank of China show that the total net outflow on the
capital account of Taiwan's balance of payments amounted to Dollars 61.9bn
from 1987 to 1991, third only to Japan and Germany.
Mr Siew said the CEPD hoped that the measures 'could effectively solve a
wide range of problems faced by private investors such as access to land,
labour supply and higher technology.
