<HEADLINE>
FT  01 JUL 93 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Australian selling season ended last week with the market indicator at
444c/kg, seven cents higher than at the end of the previous week, but
tending to soften a fraction at the close. The final weeks of the season saw
small and erractic fluctuations but no resumption of the strong rise which
led to improvement in buying activity throughout the industry at the end of
April. Holidays and the lack of auction test of wool prices are likely to
mean a dull and static market in the forthcoming weeks.
